sformations caused by modernization. Hashimoto examines writers’ anachronistic engagement with past cultures deemed obsolete or antithetical to new systems of values, showing that this transnational process was integral to the emergence of modern literature.A groundbreaking cross-cultural excavation of the origins of modern literature in East Asia featuring remarkable linguistic scope, Afterlives of Letters bridges Asian studies and comparative literature and delivers a remapping of world literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aEast Asian literaturey19th centuryxHistory and criticism2DLC. 0aEast Asian literaturey19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEast Asian literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism2DLC. 0aEast Asian literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074967008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishz978311131918608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z978311131826440uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/hash2115240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231558952423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231558952/original  a978-3-11-074967-0  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131826-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131918-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aG